  • Constructor Details

    • EmedDisEntryDigest

      public EmedDisEntryDigest(Instant dispenseTime, UUID documentId, @Nullable AuthorDigest documentAuthor, @Nullable AuthorDigest sectionAuthor, UUID entryId, UUID medicationTreatmentId, int sequence, @Nullable String annotationComment, DispenseSupplyType dispenseType, boolean otc, @Nullable EmedReference mtpEntryRef, @Nullable EmedReference preEntryRef, MedicationProduct product, @Nullable RegularUnitCodeAmbu quantityUnit, String quantityValue, @Nullable String patientMedicationInstructions, @Nullable String fulfilmentNotes, boolean inReserve, @Nullable MedicationDosageInstructions dosageInstructions)
      Constructor.
      Parameters:
      dispenseTime - The dispense time.
      documentId - The parent document unique ID.
      documentAuthor - The author of the original parent document or null if they're not known.
      sectionAuthor - The author of the original parent section or null if they're not known.
      entryId - The item entry ID.
      medicationTreatmentId - The ID of the medication treatment this item entry belongs to.
      sequence - The sequence of addition.
      annotationComment - The annotation comment or null if it isn't provided.
      dispenseType - The dispense type (first fill or refill, complete or partial).
      otc - Whether the dispense is an over-the-counter (OTC) dispense (targeting the MTP) or a regular one (targeting a PRE).
      mtpEntryRef - The targeted MTP entry reference or null.
      preEntryRef - The targeted PRE entry reference or null if it's an over-the-counter dispense.
      product - The dispensed medication product.
      quantityUnit - The dispensed medication quantity unit, if any.
      quantityValue - The dispensed medication quantity value.
      patientMedicationInstructions - The patient medication instructions or null if it isn't provided.
      fulfilmentNotes - The fulfilment notes or null if it isn't provided.
      inReserve - Whether the treatment is to be taken regularly (false) or only if required (true).
      dosageInstructions - The changed dosage instructions or null if they haven't changed.
